byline.original: Correspondence of the New-York Daily Times

lead_paragraph: The supplies of FLOUR continue small. There has been an increased export demand, and 1,500 bbls. fresh ground, have been disposed of, part straight brands at $4 06@$4 12 1/2 ?? bbl. There is a fair demand for the supply of the city trade at $4 12 1/2 2$4 25 for common and good brands, and $4 31 1/4@$4 75 for select brands and extra. In RYE FLOUR no further sales have been reported.
